raight sides and five interior angles. In a regular pentagon, all sides are=
 of equal length, and each interior angle measures 108 degrees. Pentagons c=
an also be irregular, where side lengths and angles may differ. The shape i=
s commonly found in nature, architecture, and design and is often associate=
d with symmetry and balance.<br><br>
